          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/eu-funding-radio-free-europe-czech-republic-leads-effort.png" alt="RFE/RL's corporate headquarters are in Washington, and its journalistic headquarters are in the Czech Republic, which has been leading the EU drive to find funds" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>RFE/RL's corporate headquarters are in Washington, and its journalistic headquarters are in the Czech Republic, which has been leading the EU drive to find funds. Credits: AP Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
     The European Union has approved $6.3M in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-spotlights-h1-1-emergency-funding?source=website" target="_blank">emergency funding</a> to keep Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty (RFE/RL) afloat. EU foreign policy chief Kaja Kallas said the bloc has been looking for "strategic areas" to help as the United States slashes foreign aid. She hoped 27 EU member states would provide more funds to support Radio Free Europe in the long term.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      She announced the emergency aid as a short-term ‚Äúsafety net‚Äù to support independent journalism, particularly in countries near the EU that rely on external news sources. Reflecting on her experience in Soviet-era Estonia, Kallas called RFE/RL ‚Äú<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-may-25-spotlights-h1-2-a-beacon-of-democracy?source=website" target="_blank">a beacon of democracy</a>‚Äù and said it was vital for delivering uncensored news.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        The US government's funding cut, which the outlet accused of liberal bias, threatened to shut down the broadcaster by June. A US federal judge ordered the Trump administration to restore $12M in previously approved funding.</p>
       
